Clean NPI Entries Function

clean_npi_entries.Rd

This function cleans NPI search results by normalizing credentials, applying filters for taxonomies, and summarizing entries by NPI. It includes console logging of key steps.

Usage

clean_npi_entries(
  npi_entries,
  basic_credentials = c("MD", "DO"),
  taxonomy_filter = "Obstetrics & Gynecology"
)

Arguments

npi_entries

A dataframe containing NPI search results.

basic_credentials

A character vector of credentials to filter by (default is c("MD", "DO")).

taxonomy_filter

A string for filtering taxonomies (default is "Obstetrics & Gynecology").

Value

A cleaned dataframe with summarized NPI entries.

Examples

# Example 1: Basic cleaning of NPI entries with default parameters
clean_npi_entries(npi_results)
